    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom are turning kinda yellow and pale compared to the top ones. what's probably going on with them?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "There are several reasons why the leaves on the bottom of your tomato plants might be turning yellow and pale. Overwatering or soil that's too rich in nitrogen can cause the upper leaves to thrive while the lower leaves receive less nutrients and become stressed, leading to yellowing. Additionally, inadequate air circulation or an excessive amount of sunlight can also lead to this issue. However, one common cause is the natural process of leaf drop as the plant grows and produces new foliage.",
